THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF NEVADA, REPRESENTED IN
SENATE AND ASSEMBLY, DO ENACT AS FOLLOWS:
1 Section 1. Chapter 1 of NRS is hereby amended by adding
2 thereto the provisions set forth as sections 1.3 and 1.7 of this act.
3 Sec. 1.3. 1. The Legislature hereby finds and declares that
4 access to justice and the courts of this State is of great importance
5 to the people of this State, and the Legislature recognizes the
6 interest of the courts in maintaining order and decorum in the
7 courtroom.
8 2. The Legislature therefore urges the courts of this State, for
9 the purpose of recognizing the diverse socioeconomic
10 backgrounds of the people who appear before them, not to create
11 policies, rules or administrative orders that unduly restrict access
12 to justice based on the attire of the parties, witnesses or public.
13 Sec. 1.7. 1. A court may not impose a penalty on a
14 defendant who is denied access to a courtroom solely because the
15 defendant is not wearing formal or professional attire.
16 2. As used in this section:
17 (a) “Formal or professional attire” includes, without
18 limitation, suits, trousers, slacks, long pants, dress shirts, long-
19 sleeved shirts, suit jackets, blazers, ties, dresses, skirts, pantsuits,
20 dress shoes and closed-toed shoes.
21 (b) “Penalty” includes, without limitation:
22 (1) A fine or fee;
23 (2) Entering upon the minutes that a person failed to
24 appear when lawfully required in court; or
25 (3) The issuance of a warrant for arrest.
26 Sec. 2. (Deleted by amendment.)
27 Sec. 3. (Deleted by amendment.)
28 Sec. 4. (Deleted by amendment.)
29 Sec. 5. Chapter 213 of NRS is hereby amended by adding
30 thereto a new section to read as follows:
31 1. The Division may, by regulation, establish a pilot program
32 to identify and develop employment opportunities for and provide
33 training on employment readiness to parolees and probationers.
34 2. In establishing the pilot program, the Division may
35 collaborate with nonprofit organizations in the community that
36 provide services to parolees and probationers.
37 Sec. 6. NRS 213.107 is hereby amended to read as follows:
38 213.107 As used in NRS 213.107 to 213.157, inclusive, and
39 section 5 of this act, unless the context otherwise requires:
40 1. “Board” means the State Board of Parole Commissioners.
41 2. “Chief” means the Chief Parole and Probation Officer.
